      <biogHist id="md5-ef403d919dbbe134a1c21c209ea672c3">
        <p>St. Regis (Alberta) Ltd. began as North Western Pulp and Power Ltd., a subsidiary of the St. Regis Paper Company of New York, incorporated in 1951. It became St. Regis (Alberta) Inc. in 1978 and since then has had two more corporate changes: to Champion Forest Products (Alberta) Ltd. when it was bought by Champion International in 1985, and to Weldwood of Canada, Hinton Division, in 1988.  This Hinton-based firm manufactures wood pulp and other forest products.</p>
      </biogHist>
